    bf:summary [ a bf:Summary ;
            rdfs:label "\"An in-depth look at the 8-bit AVR architecture found in ATtiny and ATmega microcontrollers, mainly from a software and programming point of view. Explore the AVR architecture using C and assembly language in Microchip Studio (formerly Atmel Studio) with ATtiny microcontrollers. Learn the details of how AVR microcontrollers work internally, including the internal registers and memory map of ATtiny devices. Program ATtiny microcontrollers using an Atmel-ICE-programmer / debugger, or use a cheap hobby programmer, or even an Arduino Uno as a programmer. Most code examples can be run using the Microchip Studio AVR simulator. Learn to write programs for ATtiny microcontrollers in assembly language. See how assembly language is converted to machine code instructions by the assembler program. Find out how programs written in the C programming language end up as assembly language and finally as machine code instructions. Use the Microchip Studio debugger in combination with a hardware USB programmer / debugger to test assembly and C language programs, or use the Microchip Studio AVR simulator. DIP packaged ATtiny microcontrollers are used in this volume for easy use on electronic breadboards, targeting mainly the ATtiny13(A) and ATtiny25/45/85. Learn about instruction timing and clocks in AVR microcontrollers using ATtiny devices. Be on your way to becoming an AVR expert with advanced debugging and programming skills.\"-- Taken from back cover."@en ] ;
    bf:supplementaryContent <http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/msupplcont/index> ;
    bf:tableOfContents [ a bf:TableOfContents ;
            rdfs:label "Arithmetic and Logic Instructions. Positive and negative numbers ; Addition ; Subtraction ; Logic instructions ; Other arithmetic and logic instructions ; Summary --Programming AVR I/O Ports. Instructions for accessing I/O registers ; I/O ports ; Summary -- Assembly Language Elements. Instructions and labels ; The preprocessor and include files ; Assembler directives ; Other assembly language elements ; Further reading ; Summary -- AVR Timing, Timers and Interrupts. Instruction timing ; Assembly language time delay ; Calling an assembly subroutine from C code ; Polled timer delay ; Timer interrupt delay ; Summary -- The AVR Instruction Set. AVR instruction set overview and categories ; Guided tour through the ATtiny AVR instruction set ; Entire AVR instruction set -- Software Tools and Settings. AVR assembler programs ; The GNU C toolchain ; Where to from here? -- Appendix A. External Programmer Setup. Hobby USB programmer capabilities ; Overview of external programmer setup ; External programmer setup -- Appendix B. Alternate Circuits and Programs. 8-pin PDIP ATtiny13/25/45/85 ; 14-pin PDIP ATtiny24/44/84 ; 20-pin PDIP ATtiny26/261/461/861 and ATtiny2313/4313 ; 28-pin PDIP ATtiny48/88 ; Alternate programs -- Appendix C. The ASCII Table. Printable characters ; ASCII Tables." ],
        [ a bf:TableOfContents ;
            rdfs:label "Introduction. Broad overview of this book ; About the targeted AVR microcontrollers ; Primary programming software ; Why learn assembly language? ; The many reasons for learning assembly language ; C programming ; Intended audience ; Prerequisites ; Microchip, Atmel, Microchip Studio and Atmel Studio ; Accompanying resources ; Let's get started -- Overview of ATtiny Microcontrollers. ATtiny microcontrollers ; Which ATtiny to use ; Comparison of ATtiny devices ; Summary -- Hardware and Software Setup. Install Microchip Studio ; 8-pin ATtiny microcontroller LED circuit ; A first assembly language program ; A first C program ; Summary -- Basics of Assembly Language. Mnemonics ; AVR instruction set ; Opcodes and operands ; Assembly language comments ; LED blink program operation ; Using the debugger and simulator ; Summary -- Binary Numbers and Memory. Bits and bytes ; Weighted number systems ; Hexadecimal numbers ; Calculating number sizes ; Numbers in assembly programs ; Numbers in C programs ; Summary -- AVR Registers and Memory Map. AVR registers ; Using general purpose registers ; AVR memory map ;  Accessing SRAM in assembler programs ; Summary -- AVR Internal Architecture. Clock pulses and program counter ; Microcontroller buses ; Harvard and von Neumann architectures ; Fetching and executing instructions ; Status register ; Stack and stack pointer ; LED blink program fully explained ; AVR instruction encoding ; Addressing modes ; Summary --" ] ;
    bf:title [ a bf:Title ;
            rdfs:label "Explore ATtiny microcontrollers using C and assembly language :" ;
            bflc:nonSortNum "0" ;
            bf:mainTitle "Explore ATtiny microcontrollers using C and assembly language :" ] .

